===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|水|alt1=氵|t1=water|九|t2=hook|木|t3=tree|ls=ic}} – to hang (on a hook 九) from a tree (木) into water (氵), so as to dye.

Earlier forms more often graphically {{Han compound|水|杂|alt1=氵}}; in the modern form, the water radical is moved upward to the upper-left corner.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Coblin (1986)}} compares this to {{cog|bo|ཉམས་པ||be stained, tarnished, spoiled}}; {{zh-ref|Pan (1987)}} also notes {{cog|tai-pro|*ɲuɔmᴬ}} as well as {{cog|vi|nhuộm}}, both meaning "to dye".

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} cites {{zh-ref|Downer (1986)}}'s opinion that form with {{zh-l|上}} tone is the verb, while form with {{zh-l|去}} tone is the noun meaning "kind of cloth" ({{w|Book of Rites|Lǐjì}}).

